:R-HSA-8932504  a           owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0006493 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Core M2 glycans are initiated by beta-1,6-linked GlcNAc extension of core M1 glycans. These structures are primarily found in brain and prostate tissue and account for no more than 5% of brain protein-linked O-glycans. M2 structures play a role in neural cell adhesion and migration (Praissman & Wells 2014; Endo, 2019)." ;
        rdfs:label          "DAG1 core M2 glycosylations" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2016-07-26" , "Reviewed: Zaru, Rossana, 2025-05-01" , "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2016-07-26" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
